            "text_tip2": {
              "type": "text",
              "settings": {
                "text": "<p>This is where most people go wrong. In winter, your succulents are dormant or semi-dormant. They're not growing, so they're barely using any water. Yet we continue watering them on the same schedule as summer.</p><p><strong>Here's your new winter watering rule: water deeply but infrequently—maybe once a month, or even less.</strong></p><p>Wait until the compost is completely dry all the way through. I mean bone-dry. Stick your finger deep into the pot—if there's even a hint of moisture, don't water. The leaves will tell you when they need a drink; they'll start to wrinkle slightly. That's your cue.</p>",
