            "text_tip5": {
              "type": "text",
              "settings": {
                "text": "<p>Keep an eye out for these red flags:</p><ul><li><strong>Translucent, mushy leaves</strong> – Overwatering damage</li><li><strong>Black or brown soggy stems</strong> – Root rot spreading upwards</li><li><strong>Leaves dropping off easily</strong> – Sign of rot or extreme overwatering</li><li><strong>Compost stays wet for days</strong> – Time to repot into grittier mix</li></ul><p>Catch these early, and you might be able to save your plant by reducing water, improving drainage, or taking healthy cuttings to propagate.</p>",
